@* Notes for InteropDemo.razor
1.	Purpose
•	Demonstrates isolated JavaScript module interop from a Blazor component using import and ES module calls.
2.	Services & injections
•	@inject IJSRuntime JS — injects the Blazor JavaScript runtime used to load and call JS modules.
3.	UI
•	<h3>InteropDemo</h3> — component title.
•	<button @onclick="Show">Show Isolated JS</button> — triggers the Show method on click.
4.	Module reference
•	private IJSObjectReference? _module; — nullable reference to the loaded JS module (ES module). Stores the module instance for 
later invocations.
5.	Lifecycle and module loading
•	protected override async Task OnAfterRenderAsync(bool firstRender) — uses this lifecycle method because JS interop that 
touches DOM should run after first render.
•	if (firstRender) ensures the module is imported only once.
•	_module = await JS.InvokeAsync<IJSObjectReference>("import", "./Components/InteropDemo.razor.js"); — dynamically imports 
    the ES module at the specified relative path and stores the returned IJSObjectReference.
6.	Calling JS
•	async Task Show() — invoked by the button.
•	await _module!.InvokeVoidAsync("showMessage", "Hello Isolated JS"); — calls the showMessage export from the imported module. 
Uses the null-forgiving operator ! because _module is nullable but expected to be non-null after first render. *@
